<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Thormael on 05-30-2000 07:41 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Stats are pretty obvious to everyone.
Erudites and humans have no night vision, dark elves have ultravision, all the other clerical races have infravision. (vision can be a real pain sometimes, try to get the ring from Sol A, and/or find a mage to summon you a heat/cold stone when you log)
Faction depends a lot on race and deity of course, but I know some don't care (quest rely heavily on it though). I think Erudites, Gnomes and Humans can be "good" or "evil". Dark Elves are evil, the others are good.
Then halflings can hide and sneak, dark elves can hide, gnomes can tinker, these are important abilites. Hide is cool if you need to rest invis, cause we cannot invis. Sneak is great to deal with NPCs (buy/sell) and can also be used to actually sneak (hehe, hard but possible). Tinkering can be fun if you like trades and toys. Few of the things you'll make will be useful too.
Then comes the look. High elves and dwarves look awful, must be to counter their awesome stats. The other races look cool to very cool in plate (erudites have a very unique look).
Items and quest wise I think humans are the best for now.
I'm human, and if I had to reroll my char, I'm not sure if I'd go for human again, I like gnomes and halflings (gnomes are cooler but halflings have better stats/abilities). Then dark elves / erudites are nice also. High elves / dwarves come last, they look ugly (well, females high elves can look ok in some cases) and are the stats obvious choice, which I tend to dislike, personnaly.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
